The paper discusses the concept of a knowledge-based economy and the Triple Helix model, which are both related to the field of computer science and information technology. Specifically, the paper explores the role of knowledge as a social coordination mechanism and the restructuring of knowledge production in a knowledge-based economy. It also discusses the systems-of-innovation approach and neo-evolutionary theories of innovation, which are relevant to the field of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
